WYSIWYM.ontology
Class OntologyReader

java.lang.Object
  WYSIWYM.ontology.OntologyReader
Direct Known Subclasses:
GeographyOntologyReader, SpecificationOntologyReader
public class OntologyReader
extends Object

OntologyEditor wraps a Jena class OntModel and provides information about this ontology, e.g. which properties a class can (and must) have, what the domain and range of properties are, what the cardinality restrictions on a class are, comments, etc.

Version:
1.1 20-10-2006, 1.5 21-08-2008
Author:
Feikje Hielkema

OntologyReader

public OntologyReader()
               throws OntologyInputException
Default constructor. Imports all three PolicyGrid ontologies into one Jena model, and sets the appropriate prefixes. This is the constructor that LIBER uses.

initMaps

protected void initMaps()
Creates various HashMaps that store information about local names, domains and ranges of classes and properties, which is needed by many of LIBER's methods. This method takes 10 sec. to run, but saves a lot of time later on!

getCompulsoryStringProperties

public Map<String,String[]> getCompulsoryStringProperties(OntClass c)
Takes a class and returns a HashMap with as keys all 'string datatype' properties that have a minimum cardinality restriction on this class. If the property has restricted values, these are returned as a value in an array. LIBER uses this method to generate miniature forms, to quickly create an object and specify the most important information.

Parameters:
c - OntClass
Returns:
Map with property names and restricted values.

getRangeType

public Integer getRangeType(String property)
Returns an integer indicating the type of range of this property. 0 if it is no property; 1 for a datatype property with restricted values; 2 for a date; 3 for a double or float; 4 for an integer; 5 for a boolean; 6 for a string; and 7 for another object.

Parameters:
property - Property name
Returns:
Integer
